sim.util.media.chart

Class NumberXBoxAndWhiskerXYDataset

          • sim.util.media.chart.NumberXBoxAndWhiskerXYDataset
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.ObjectInputValidation, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.EventListener, org.jfree.data.general.Dataset, org.jfree.data.general.SeriesChangeListener, org.jfree.data.general.SeriesDataset, org.jfree.data.RangeInfo, org.jfree.data.statistics.BoxAndWhiskerXYDataset, org.jfree.data.xy.XYDataset

    public class NumberXBoxAndWhiskerXYDataset
extends org.jfree.data.xy.AbstractXYDataset
implements org.jfree.data.statistics.BoxAndWhiskerXYDataset, org.jfree.data.RangeInfo
    This is an alternative to JFreeChart's DefaultBoxAndWhiskerXYDataset, which use Date for X values. I want a Number axis, so here it is. On a different issue, DefaultBoxAndWhiskerXYDataset allows a single series. No point in having multiple series here, they'd be rendered with the same color (the renderer uses the same colors for all series and it would be too difficult and non-elegant to extend) On the down side, I'll have to handle deleting series through deleting datasets. At least I don't depend on copying any code that would change in future releases (e.g. I better provide this implementation of an interface than an alternative to the B&W renderer). I need to implement RangeInfo, or the outliers might land outside the plot. OK, IT'S NOT FOR THE OUTLIERS, THEY'RE IGNORED IN DefaultBoxAndWhiskerXYDataset, SO I IGNORE THEM HERE TOO. I could maintain the range and update it as data is added; however I need to handle deletes, too, so O(n) is unavoidable. I iterate and build the range, then cache it and reuse it till the next change occurs. I got a few behavioral things from DefaultBoxAndWhiskerXYDataset: -the default values for outlier and farout coefficients -ignoring the "includeInterval" in the functions from the RangeInfo interface -the description says "includeInterval = a flag that determines whether or not the y-interval is taken into account." Not sure what it means, but since the code ignores it, so do I. DefaultBoxAndWhiskerXYDataset gets/sets farout and outlier coefficients, yet they ARE NOT USED. The BoxAndWhisker Item Calculator that comes with Jfreechart uses hardcoded values for those coefficients. No point in porting that here. If the calculator will ever allow the parametrization of those values, one can have add those as fields to the series attributes and have each series cache the entire data (not just the distribution stats) and recompute the all the past items when the user changes those values (just like with changing the number of bins in the histogram charts).
